{{fr-noun|f}}

# the quality of being provided [[gratis]], of being [[free of charge]]
#: {{ux|fr|La '''gratuité''' de l'école publique en France.|The '''fact that''' public school '''is free of charge''' in France.}}
# the quality of being [[gratuitous]] (unwarranted or unjustified); [[gratuitousness]]
#: {{ux|fr|La '''gratuité''' de son hypothèse affaiblit cette théorie.|The '''gratuitousness''' of its hypothesis weakens this theory.}}
# the quality of being [[gratuitous]] (without necessity or reason); [[gratuitousness]]
#: {{ux|fr|La '''gratuité''' de ce meurtre me rend malade.|The '''gratuitousness''' of that murder makes me sick.}}
#: {{ux|fr|La '''gratuité''' de l'art pour l'art.|The '''gratuitousness''' of art for art's sake.}}

====Usage notes====
* ''Gratuité'' is a false friend and never a synonym for [[gratuity]]. (Its closest English equivalent would be the rare neologisms "[[gratisness]]", "[[free of chargeness]]", or "[[freeness of charge]]".)
